{"word":"G2176 - εὐώνυμος - euṓnymos - yoo-o'-noo-mos - Left","slug":"G2176","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">εὐώνυμος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>euṓnymos"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yoo-o'-noo-mos"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Left"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B5;&#x03C5;&#x0313;&#x03C9;&#x0301;&#x03BD;&#x03C5;&#x03BC;&#x03BF;&#x03C2; - euo&#x0304;numos</b> - <i>yoo-o'-noo-mos</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G2095\">G2095</a> and <a href=\"#/G3686\">G3686</a>; properly <i>well named</i> (<i>good omened</i>), that is, the <i>left</i> (which was the <i>lucky</i> side among the pagan Greeks); neuter as adverb <i>at the left</i> hand: - (on the) left."}]}